<h3>&nbsp;</h3>
<h3>DE RADICALISATION</h3>
<p>=&nbsp;changing an individualâ€™s belief system, rejecting the extremist ideology, and embracing mainstream values.</p>
<h3><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">way forward&nbsp;</span></h3>
<h5><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">soft to hard to hybrid approaches</span></h5>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">HYBRID = </span>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">WHAM - winning heart and minds = <em><strong>Operation Sadbhavana, 1998 JnK rural areas (education , health infra)&nbsp;</strong></em></span></li>
<li>Back to village programme in JnK</li>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">Governance , poverty improve</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">NGO = ?&nbsp;</span></li></ul></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">SOFT&nbsp;</span>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">put the radicalised person under guidance charismatic person</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">community centres with sense of ownership = youth meet + monitor radicalistion</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">prevent religious indoctrination - (PYQ, 2015)</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">removal of relative deprivation</span></li></ul></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">HARD&nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">IR examples -&nbsp;Jordan has launched the Aqaba process to promote de-radicalisation from radical Islamic ideology in which India is an active participant.</span></li></ul>
